<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 2:41PM MDT  by NWS Boise</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Twin
Falls and eastern Jerome Counties through 330 PM MDT...
At 241 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Murtaugh, or 16 miles southeast of Twin Falls, moving northeast at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Murtaugh around 250 PM MDT.
Hazelton, Eden and Milner Dam around 310 PM MDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
